# Naming & Lore

## Example
```java
ItemStack sword = new ItemStack(Material.DIAMOND_SWORD);
ItemMeta meta = sword.getItemMeta();
meta.setDisplayName("§6Epic Sword");
meta.setLore(Arrays.asList("Sharp and shiny", "Handle with care"));
sword.setItemMeta(meta);
player.getInventory().addItem(sword);
```

## Logic
- ItemMeta stores display name, lore, enchantments, etc.
- setItemMeta() applies the changes

## Edge Cases
- Some items cannot have certain meta (e.g., AIR)
- Too long lore may overflow chat

# Adding Enchantments

## Example
```java
ItemStack sword = new ItemStack(Material.DIAMOND_SWORD);
ItemMeta meta = sword.getItemMeta();
meta.addEnchant(Enchantment.DAMAGE_ALL, 5, true);
meta.addItemFlags(ItemFlag.HIDE_ENCHANTS);
sword.setItemMeta(meta);
player.getInventory().addItem(sword);
```

## Logic
- addEnchant(Enchantment, level, ignoreLevelRestriction)
- ItemFlag hides visuals like enchantment glow

## Edge Cases
- Level too high → may break balance
- Some enchantments incompatible with certain items

# Listening to Block Events

## Example: Detect Block Break
```java
@EventHandler
public void onBlockBreak(BlockBreakEvent event) {
    Block block = event.getBlock();
    if (block.getType() == Material.DIAMOND_BLOCK) {
        event.setDropItems(false);
        block.getWorld().dropItemNaturally(block.getLocation(), new ItemStack(Material.EMERALD, 2));
    }
}
```

## Logic
- Detect block type
- Cancel or modify drops
- Spawn custom items

## Edge Cases
- Event may be cancelled by other plugins
- Too many drops → lag
